gomodel:SYNGO_276  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" , "Rationale: In this paper, the authors copurified VAMP-1 together with synaptic vesicles that were isolated from electric-organ tissue of Torpedo california (Fig. 3). Moreover, they used partial proteolysis by trypsin to show that Vamp1 is an integral membrane protein of synaptic vesicles (Fig. 4)\n\n5/2/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: T. californica were kept undisturbed for 3 days before use. Animals were anesthetized by addition of tricaine to the seawater at a final concentration of 0.25 g/liter. Electric-organ tissue was removed and quickfrozen in liquid nitrogen.\n\n20/6/2018 Frank\n- uniprot accesion selected following blast (100% match) against protein sequence listed in Figure 1B." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_276" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_7787" .

